FBIS3-37122 "drsov030_s_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Georgia Receives Prospective Ministers LD1402155694 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1100 GMT 14 Feb 94 LD1402155694 Tbilisi IBERIA Language: Georgian Article Type:BFN [Text] Tbilisi, 14 Feb -- IBERIA reports that Georgian head of state E. Shevardnadze, regards Major General Joni Pirtskhalaishvili as one of the candidates for the post of defense minister. He was appointed Georgia's defense minister in Gamsakhurdia's government. E. Shevardnadze has recently invited J. Pirtskhalaishvili from Russia and had a private conversation with him. A second candidate for the post of defense minister is Maj-Gen V. Nadibaidze, currently first deputy commander in chief of the Russian troops in the Transcaucasus.
